Monday is the third and final day of the annual schoolboy Easter rugby festivals that are held across South Africa. After an interrupted programme over the last two years because of the Covid-19 pandemic, the festivals have been back with a bang in 2022. Here are all the results from the first two days of action at the four biggest festivals in South Africa – held at Kearsney, St John’s, KES and St Stithians.  Also, find all the fixtures for Monday’s final day of action. KES – day oneTrinityhouse 12 Northcliff 40Nico Malan 21 Durbanville 52Ben Vorster 22 Centurion 12Jeppe Invitational 12 Eldoraigne 20KES 37 Queen’s 36Northwood 25 Hudson Park 19 KES – day twoCenturion 7 Durbanville 66Trinityhouse 5 Nico Malan 26Ben Vorster 3 Eldoraigne 33Northwood 3 Queen’s 22Jeppe 16 Hudson Park 10KES 32 Dale College 3 Fixtures – day three (Monday) Northwood v Centurion 8am Queen’s v Durbanville 9.15am Jeppe v Dale 10.20am Ben Vorster v Nico Malan 11.30am Hudson Park v Trinityhouse 12.40pm KES v Eldoraigne 13.50pm St Stithians – day oneSt Andrew’s 29 St Alban’s 15Maritzburg 32 Michaelhouse 33Clifton 10 St Stithians 15Parktown 7 Wynberg 49Grey High 20 Bishops 31 St Stithians – day twoSt Alban’s 19-34 Grey HighSt Andrew’s 13-12 WynbergClifton 20-14 ParktownMaritzburg College 10-31 BishopsMichaelhouse 36-3 St Stithians Fixtures – day three (Monday) Clifton v Wynberg 9.15am Bishops v Parktown 10.30am Maritzburg College v Grey High 11.45am St Alban’s v Michaelhouse 1pm St Stithian’s v St Andrews 3.15pm St John’s – day oneHelpmekaar 7 Graeme 10Paarl Boys’ High 83 Lions Invitational 0Hilton 62 St Benedict’s 3Boland Landbou 25 Noordheuwel 25St Charles 12 St David’s 19Paul Roos 50 Welkom Gim 6St John’s 5 Nelspruit 24 St John’s – day twoNoordheuwel 60 St David’s 5Boland Landbou 38 St Charles 0St Benedict’s 38 Lions Invitational 21Graeme College 28 St John’s 7Hilton College 48 Welkom Gim 3Paul Roos 40 Nelspruit 3Paarl Boys’ High 32 Helpmekaar 16 Fixtures – day three (Monday) St Benedict’s v St